headline: Costco Wholesale (NasdaqGS:COST) Sees 6% Dip Despite Q2 2025 Revenue Rising To US$63,723 Million
summary: Costco Wholesale (NasdaqGS:COST) reported significant financial growth for the second quarter of 2025, with revenue climbing to USD 63,723 million and net income increasing slightly to USD 1,788 million, yet the stock saw a 5.94% decline last quarter. Despite positive earnings and increased sales, market volatility and broader economic concerns, such as the heightened tariffs announced recently, have influenced overall investor sentiment negatively.
